 <item> <title>The Legacy of the Coleman Report</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/speeches/legacy-coleman-report</link>
 <description>At Johns Hopkins University, U.S. Secretary of Education John B. King, Jr., observed the 50th anniversary of the Coleman Report and discussed the report&#039;s relevance for policy and practice today. The Secretary also  discussed the Obama Administration&#039;s efforts to improve education for disadvantaged students, promote diversity in schools, and work with states to implement the Every Student Succeeds Act.</description>
