 <item> <title>Leading the Way</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/speeches/leading-way</link>
 <description>In a speech at the National Charter School Conference in Nashville, Tenn., U.S. Secretary of Education John B. King, Jr. called for charter schools to become leaders in rethinking student discipline so that more students remain in the classroom and have the opportunity to learn. The charter sector, like traditional public schools, is showing improvement in this area, but there is more work to be done to ensure all students are in the classroom learning every day. King urged charter schools to focus on innovating to lead the way for our children. Remarks are as prepared.
</description>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.ed.gov/news/speeches/leading-way</guid>
